The paper proposes an end-to-end model for image retrieval based on deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The model also involves learning algorithms to optimize the sparsity of the generated model, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed model on image search datasets, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of bag-of-words (BoWs) model, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
